THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS

This software bundles or links to the following third-party components,
each under its own license:

- FFmpeg (https://ffmpeg.org) — LGPL-2.1+. Bundled binaries from
  gyan.dev's "essentials" build are LGPL with no GPL components.
  We invoke FFmpeg as a subprocess; we do not statically link against it.

- ONNX Runtime (https://onnxruntime.ai) — MIT License. Optional dependency,
  enabled at build time via the `onnx` Cargo feature.

- AI models (Real-ESRGAN, RIFE, GFPGAN, BasicVSR, DeepFilterNet) —
  individual licenses; check each model's source repository before
  redistributing model weights.

- Tauri (https://tauri.app) — Apache-2.0 / MIT dual.

- Rust crates listed in src-tauri/Cargo.lock — see each crate's individual
  license.

LIMITATIONS OF USE

This software is intended for personal recovery of damaged optical media
that the user owns. Users are responsible for ensuring their use complies
with copyright law in their jurisdiction. The software does not include
CSS decryption or other DRM-circumvention features.
